Milena Ercolani (born 19 September 1963) is a Sammarinese poet and novelist. An alumna of the Antica Universit√† Picena, she is a teacher. She is active in the literary life of her country, and has represented San Marino at numerous literary events around the world. She has written since childhood, and has also produced stories for children. Her work has won numerous prizes. She is the president of the Sammarina Cultural Association, which promotes the artistic work of San Marino and the surrounding region.
